Linux Learning Summary
1. Core Linux Fundamentals

Linux File System Hierarchy

Shell and system concepts

Critical directories important for patching

Linux vulnerabilities (kernel, software, network, misconfiguration, authentication issues)


2. User, Identity and Privilege Management

User handling and account management

Linux identity management

User privilege management (sudo)

File permissions (read, write, execute)

Special permissions (SUID, SGID, Sticky bit)

Access Control Lists (ACL)


3. Package and Service Management

Package managers: yum, dnf, apt

Installing, updating and removing packages

Systemd and service management

Daemon processes

4. Process and CPU Management

Process creation (fork & exec)

Process hierarchy

Process states

Process scheduling and priority

Foreground & background processes

5. Memory Management

Virtual memory concepts

Free, used and available memory

Buffers and cache

Swap memory and shared memory

Out-Of-Memory (OOM)

6. Disk and Storage Management

Disks and storage devices

Partition creation

Filesystem creation

Mounting filesystems

Logical Volume Manager (LVM)

Prepare system for LVM

Create volumes

Format and mount logical volumes

Remove LVM

7. RAID and Shared Storage

Creating RAID arrays

Creating filesystem on RAID

Mounting RAID storage

8. Backup and Compression

Backup concepts

File compression techniques

9. Networking and Remote Access

Network adapter configuration (AlmaLinux & Ubuntu)

Name resolution configuration

SSH server and client installation

Secure remote access configuration

Linux firewall configuration and rules

10. Automation and Scheduling

Cron jobs configuration

User cron jobs and system cron jobs

Scheduling tasks (daily, weekly, specific date)

11. Scripting and Command-line Skills

Searching files using grep

Working with regular expressions

Interactive and non-interactive scripts

Scripts using loops and conditions

12. Containers and Version Control

Running containers on Linux

Container automation

Creating Git repositories

Version control using Git

13. System Administration Skills Practiced

Package management troubleshooting

Process management tasks

Service management tasks

Disk management and memory management

Remote connectivity management

Shared storage management
